Billye Jess MYERS v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5067. United States Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 7, 1955. No appearance for appellant. Paul W. Cress, U. S. Atty., and H. Dale Cook, Asst. U. S. Atty., Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and MURRAH and PICKETT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed on motion of appellee, on ground appeal was frivolous.
